ACE SF 5 Digit Number-Series SF Singles

This is an example of the ACE editions that reprinted "Science Fiction From The Great Years" Orignally published as ACE F-257 (1963).

01575-7 DAVE DUNCAN The Alchemist's Apprentice (cover by Jim Griffin; c.2007; March 2008)

01594-8 CHARLES STROSS Saturn's Children (wrap around cover by Joe Williamsen; July 2008; 1st ACE printing)

Includes stories by Issac Asimov, Fritz Leiber, Roger Zelazny, Richard Wilson, Zenna Henderson, and others.

Includes 13 stories by Philip K. Dick, Isaac Asimov, Ron Goulart, Roger Zelazny, Norman Spinrad, and others.

Includes 14 stories by J. G. Ballard, Ron Goulart, K. M. O'Donnell, Robert Sheckley, Harry Harrison, and others.

Includes Nebula and Hugo Award-winning stories as well as biographic material and essays on Theodore Sturgeon, Ray Bradbury, Isaac Asimov, Fritz Leiber, Poul Anderson, and James Blish.
